Gulf Stocks: Advanced Petrochemicals and Combined Group

-- B y   Z a h r a   H a n k i r
-- 
2011-06-13T13:19:02Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-13/gulf-stocks-advanced-petrochemicals-and-combined-group.html
Dubai’s  DFM General Index (DFMGI)  rose 0.4
percent at the 2 p.m. close in Dubai and Abu Dhabi’s  ADX General
Index (ADSMI)  gained 0.3 percent. Saudi Arabia’s  Tadawul All Share Index (SASEIDX) 
advanced 0.5 percent.  The following stocks rose or fell in the Persian Gulf
region. Symbols are in parentheses.  Advanced Petrochemicals Co. (APPC)   increased for a
second day, rising 0.6 percent to 33.7 riyals. The Saudi Arabian
chemicals producer will pay a 1-riyal dividend for the first
half of the year.  Combined Group Contracting Co. (CGC)   rose for the first
time since June 7, climbing 1.1 percent to 1,820 fils. The
construction company plans to expand operations in Saudi Arabia
and Qatar after Kuwait postponed a $2.6 billion road-building
contract the company sought in partnership with Hyundai
Engineering & Construction.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Zahra Hankir in Dubai at 
 zhankir@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Claudia Maedler at 
 cmaedler@bloomberg.net  